i was it with a revalation at work and wanted to share it<br/><br/>It was Wednesday 27 May  0530pm i am in work unloading lifts of cold chain delivery.
<br />i Started to sing one of my favorite Faith songs &quot;Did you here the mountains tremble&quot;
<br />and thinking about a few things one of them was My Pastor he said in one of the Service &quot;god likes to mix things up ,he puts loud people with quiet people and giggles and says work it out&quot;
<br />and the other thing was my friend Frank he had told me about the story of the good Samaritan.
<br />when i suddenly was hit with a revelation
<br /><br />i said  people seem to look at others and not see whats real
<br /><br />i had an image in my mind about a puzzle  there is a circle hole  and a triangle piece,
<br />the man looking a the Triangle piece was not happy as the Triangle does not fit in the circle hole.
<br /><br />Jesus comes to the man and says &quot;my son whats bothering you&quot;
<br /><br />the man annoyed said  &quot;i have this circle hole and other is this Triangle piece they don't go together&quot;
<br /><br />Jesus laughed and put his hands on the mans eyes and says &quot;look through my hands at the hole and the piece tell me what you see&quot;
<br /><br />The man looks with a confused expression on his face and says &quot;oooooh i see a square hole and a square piece that fit perfectly together&quot;
<br /><br />Jesus removed his Hands and said &quot;do you understand&quot;
<br />the Man looks and says with honesty in is heart &quot;Not really can you explain&quot;
<br /><br />Jesus said &quot;think of this puzzle as in two people one thinks he is a circle and he sees another person who he thinks is a triangle.
<br />he wont talk or help the other person as they're different and would not fit in well with them at all.
<br />he is so focused on their differences he cant see that there is a lot of similarities and could work well together in life people put themselves in categories eg rich,poor,man of faith,man who is faithless and so on.
<br />if people would stop categorizing people and start treating each other as equals the world would be so much better place to live&quot; Jesus then adds &quot;My Father loves every one,he does not care about class,race,sinner,saint he loves every one equally all he wants is for people to choose and love him too live a good life following the word of Christ,but he does not ever give up on people but people who turn back on him cant see him and feel his love,He is the Ultimate he has no limits on the blessings he can bestow on his people he is not limited by conventional laws i will give you an example i had a child come to me all upset i stopped and talked to this child and asked whats was wrong she said my  mum is ill and i want God to help her but my friends are all praying for there mother who is Dying and i don't think he will hear me. with out hesitation i looked at her and said Pray for your mum and there mum God as more power then you can ever understand he can make any thing happen he created this earth and the Galaxy and every thing in it he can help both and he works through his children and listens to all your prayers he knows your deepest thoughts and secrets Just call to him if you need him. i then went into the house to see her mother and put my hand on her head i then prayed to god and said please help this woman Father then i left. the girl came to see me two days later saying her mother was all well and she had improved after my visit i said God blessed her that day and loves to help people don't ever be afraid to ask God for help or seek his guidance he is always there he is omnipresence he is every where ,every time,forever&quot;
<br /><br />Below i have included the Parable of the good Samaritan The priest and the levite was been circles
<br />they was to focused on them selves and consider them self men of faith but would not take the time to help the man. but the Samaritan who they consider a triangle showed compassion and helped the man. on that day that samaritan showed my god like quality then the men of faith.
<br />when we look at the world like the Samaritan and we look after each other there is no triangle and circles we are all gods children and you should love and help everyone as God does.
<br /><br />God asks it to love your neighbor and with the world now as open as it is your neighbor is not just the man next door or even in same country as you its  Global your neighbor to all and all are your neighbor.
<br /><br />Luke 10:25-37
<br /><br />The Parable of the Good Samaritan
<br /> 25On one occasion an expert in the law stood up to test Jesus. &quot;Teacher,&quot; he asked, &quot;what must I do to inherit eternal life?&quot;
<br /><br />26&quot;What is written in the Law?&quot; he replied. &quot;How do you read it?&quot;
<br /><br />27He answered: &quot; 'Love the Lord your God with all your heart and with all your soul and with all your strength and with all your mind'[a]; and, 'Love your neighbor as yourself.'[b]&quot;
<br /><br />28&quot;You have answered correctly,&quot; Jesus replied. &quot;Do this and you will live.&quot;
<br /><br />29But he wanted to justify himself, so he asked Jesus, &quot;And who is my neighbor?&quot;
<br /><br />30In reply Jesus said: &quot;A man was going down from Jerusalem to Jericho, when he fell into the hands of robbers. They stripped him of his clothes, beat him and went away, leaving him half dead. 31A priest happened to be going down the same road, and when he saw the man, he passed by on the other side. 32So too, a Levite, when he came to the place and saw him, passed by on the other side. 33But a Samaritan, as he traveled, came where the man was; and when he saw him, he took pity on him. 34He went to him and bandaged his wounds, pouring on oil and wine. Then he put the man on his own donkey, took him to an inn and took care of him. 35The next day he took out two silver coins<img class="smiley" src="http://www.pan.net/smilies/coolbox.gif" alt=":)" /> and gave them to the innkeeper. 'Look after him,' he said, 'and when I return, I will reimburse you for any extra expense you may have.'
<br /><br />36&quot;Which of these three do you think was a neighbor to the man who fell into the hands of robbers?&quot;
<br /><br />37The expert in the law replied, &quot;The one who had mercy on him.&quot;
<br />      Jesus told him, &quot;Go and do likewise.&quot;
<br /><br />SO DON'T BE A TRIANGLE,CIRCLE YOUR BETTER THEN THAT AND GOD BLESS YOU ALL
